   Web Site Accessibility

      Our goal is to provide everyone with easy access to information about
      the Yucca Mountain Project.

      We are currently working to make this site accessible, in accordance
      with the guidelines contained in Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act
      of 1973 (as amended by the Workforce Reinvestment Act of 1998).

      If you have any problems accessing information contained on this site,
      please contact us at 1-800-225-6972 or submit your feedback online. We
      also welcome your suggestions for improving the accessibility features
      of our web site.

      For more information on making government web sites accessible visit
      any of the following sites:

        Federal IT Accessibility Initiative - The Federal Information
        Technology Accessibility Initiative is a federal government
        interagency effort to offer information and technical assistance to
        assist in the successful implementation of Section 508.

        The Access Board - A federal agency committed to accessible design.



